title: 5.7 earthquake felt in parts of alaska
author: Times Stafftimes News Services
text: GOLDEN, Colo. An earthquake in the registering 5.7 on the Richter scale was felt lightly in parts of Alaska yesterday morning.     The U.S. Geological Survey said the tremor was centered 150 miles southeast of Sand Point, Alaska, and about 570 miles south-southeast of Anchorage.
